-- Turkey Milk Companies Gain on Erdogan Pledge to School Children
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-03-21T11:15:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-21/turkey-milk-companies-gain-on-erdogan-pledge-to-school-children.html
Turkish dairy producers  Pinar Sut
Mamulleri Sanayii AS (PNSUT)  and  Yaprak Sut & Besi Ciftlikleri Sanayi &
Ticaret AS (YAPRK)  advanced after Prime Minister  Recep Tayyip Erdogan 
pledged to distribute milk to school children.  Pinar gained 1.9 percent to 19.30 liras, its highest in two
weeks, while Yaprak added 1.4 percent to 4.30 liras, its highest
in a month.  Erdogan said in a speech in parliament in Ankara today that
the government would begin distributing free milk to students up
to the fifth grade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
